 A long queue was seen at the SARS office this morning, while many in the line were scared that they would be standing there in vain. However, the doors opened at about 08:30 and taxpayers were able to enter the building with ease. ALSO READ: Tax and traffic worry Penny Street residents The office was closed on Friday due to ongoing strikes by SARS employees across the country. These employees are members of the Public Servants Association (PSA) and National Education, Health and Allied Workers’ Union (Nehawu), and are asking for a salary increase. Those who were standing in the queue said they hoped that the doors would open. ALSO READ: GALLERY: Funeral for Jackson Mthembu’s daughter at KaNyamazane Stadium